{
  "page": "Lady Baela",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the ship's namesake, see <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela Targaryen</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c7/Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/300px-Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c7/Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/450px-Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c7/Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/600px-Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aegon_III_and_Viserys_II_Reunion_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Larra_Rogare\" title=\"Larra Rogare\">Larra Rogare</a> emerge from the <i>Lady Baela</i> (right) © Wouter Florusse in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Lady Baela</b></i> was a war galley of two hundred oars in the <a href=\"/index.php/Velaryon_fleet\" title=\"Velaryon fleet\">Velaryon fleet</a>. It was captained by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lady_Baela&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Originally a <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavosi</a> ship, the galley was captured during <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Alyn%27s_attack\" title=\"Lord Alyn&#39;s attack\">Lord Alyn's attack</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughters%27_War\" title=\"Daughters&#39; War\">Daughters' War</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Oakenfist</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Named_after\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Named after\">renamed</a> the ship <i>Lady Baela</i> to honor his wife, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><i>Lady Baela</i> was Alyn's flagship when he sailed from <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Sea\" title=\"Sunset Sea\">Sunset Sea</a> to confront Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Dalton_Greyjoy\" title=\"Dalton Greyjoy\">Dalton Greyjoy</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, the first of his six <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Voyages\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Great Voyages\">Great Voyages</a>. When he approached the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>, Alyn left his other ships behind and sailed <i>Lady Baela</i> into <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodstone\" title=\"Bloodstone\">Bloodstone</a> to treat with <a href=\"/index.php/Racallio_Ryndoon\" title=\"Racallio Ryndoon\">Racallio Ryndoon</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Narrow_Sea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King of the Narrow Sea\">King of the Narrow Sea</a>. After spending more than a fortnight in Racallio's company, the Oakenfist was allowed to sail his fleet south to the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Alyn visited <a href=\"/index.php/Sunspear\" title=\"Sunspear\">Sunspear</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> before arriving at <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a>. During his return voyage, Alyn visited <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a> and rescued Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lady_Baela&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404004330\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.031 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.059 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 425/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8743/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2046/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1036/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1971/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.64 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   50.248      1 -total\n 57.21%   28.749      1 Template:Italic_title\n 17.98%    9.034      4 Template:Ref\n 12.71%    6.388      1 Template:For\n 11.77%    5.914      4 Template:Ref/core\n  7.87%    3.952      1 Template:Date\n  3.19%    1.603      1 Template:References\n-